oves)","100 g carrot, cut into pieces","20 g oil","40 g lime juice","10 g fish sauce","¼ tsp salt","2 tsp soy sauce","10 g sugar","50 g plum tomatoes, cut into halves","150 g fresh pineapple, flesh cut into pieces (1 cm)","1 lemon, cut into thin slices, for garnishing","fresh mint, leaves, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r179472","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-Y6NienXU-B0\/XZQGdho6IPI\/AAAAAAAAb-U\/t9FvhcMwSU8WVfUzCh5r4ifGPj5Af4NfACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_PzHO7LNPa0E0SBkV.png","title":"Hot and sour pineapple pork with turmeric rice","publishedAt":"2018-01-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"22.4 g","fat":"20.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"46.5 g","calories":"1985 kJ \/ 472 kcal"},"usefulItems":"thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to the<em> <\/em><em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or<em> <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em><\/em> for the Chicken stock paste recipe.","Reserve the turmeric liquid after cooking rice and use as a base for soups or stews."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","55m","4 portions"]}